                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 2136/349.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Furniss</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-12-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 5, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Root informs Minister Furniss that in the absence of naval vessel of any
                    European power having interests in Haiti, and upon urgent occasion or request
                    for protection, the American naval forces will afford temporary protection and
                    refuge from immediate violence in the same manner as to American citizens and
                    interests similarly menaced.</p>
            </div>
